Conditional/Decision Statement
================================
Conditional/Decision statement gives the power to take decision when to execute and what to be done
based on the condition
There are a few decision statement:
-- if
-- if..else
-- Nested if..else
-- switch

if
-------------------------
It checks the conditions if the condition is true during the execution of code

Syntax:
if(condition)
{
	code
}


if...else
---------------------------
Execute the if block if the condition is true, otherwise execute the else block

Syntax:
if(condition)
{
	code
}
else
{
	code
}


Nested if...else
---------------------------
Check every block until the condition is satisfied and execute if block is true, 
otherwise execute the else block

Syntax:
if(condition)
{
	code
}
else if(condition)
{
	code
}
else
{
	code
}


Switch statement
-------------------------------
Allows to match with multiple cases and check if the particular case if satisfied

Syntax:
switch(expression){
		case value:
					code
					break;

		case value:
					code
					break;
					
		default;
}

******FACTS*****
-- Data type should be same for comparison
-- Can have multiple cases
-- Can use only Integer, String and Enum
-- Break is optional but if not provided it will check all cases till the end
-- Default is optional